history.content:
I am currently taking IEOR 173. In general, if you are interested in machine learning stuff, you should take EE 126 as it is designed for it and you will be digging into the theory part (which is very important in ML and AI). IEOR 173 focuses on solving the real world problem by modeling and applying the theory. In its homework and exams, almost every number and matrix has meaning (eg # of products sold per day or the probability of raining tomorrow). Lastly the workload of 173 will be significantly lower than 126 as one is 3 units and the other is 4.

Note 173 has never been offered in fall, so if you want to take an stochastic process class next semester then EE 126 will be the only option between the two.
